M_ADD
public abstract class FBFunctionQS2
extends FBFunction2

The abstract superclass of all functions with a REQ/CNF event pair, a single output variable OUT, two inputs IN1 and IN2, and QI/QO/STATUS I/O.

serviceEvent

public void serviceEvent(EventServer e)
Services the specified event (always REQ for FBs of this type). Copies QI to QO. If QI=FALSE, sets STATUS to INHIBITED and issues an event at CNF. Otherwise, sets STATUS=OK, invokes req() to perform the operation (and possibly set QO=FALSE and STATUS to an appropriate value of FBStatus if an error occurs, and finally issues an event at CNF.

Specified by:
serviceEvent in interface EventServer
Overrides:
serviceEvent in class FBFunction
Parameters:
e - The event to service (always REQ for this FB type)
See Also:
EventOutput.serviceEvent(EventServer)
